Verb + Infinite

We use a verb + an infinite when we want to talk about why someone does something. 

He went to the shop to buy a newspaper. 
(The reason for going to the shop was to buy a newspaper)

She came to see me.

We study to pass our exams. 

I use a hairdryer to dry my hair.

He didn't go to the store to look for you. 

What does he want to do?

He wants to watch a movie.

Note: We use the gerund (-ing) if we want to talk about the purpose of something. 

The hairdryer is for drying my hair.

